	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Dec 25&#47;59</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Reverd. S Morais</addressee></p>
				<p><placeName>Cherry St. Synagogue Phila.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName>Mr. Abraham Harris</persName> of your city having made<lb/> application to our congregation for the situation of minister we have<lb/> invited him here on a probationary visit.  Since his arrival various<lb/> rumors have sprung up prejudicial to his character as a man a<lb/> minister or an Israelite&#44; on being informed of them <persName>Mr. H</persName> very properly<lb/> declined officiating until an oppy. was afforded for thorough investiga<lb/>&#61;tion&#44; he has given your address with that of several other gentlemen<lb/> with whom he is bid acquainted&#44; he stands before us quite a stran<lb/>&#61;ger.  Our object now is to do justice to the congregation as well as to <persName>Mr. H</persName><lb/> would therefore solicit your information on the following points<lb/> which shall be held confidential if you so desire it.</p>
				<p>Amongst other things he is charged with having preached or lec&#61;<lb/>&#61;tured in a <sic>christian</sic> pulpit or lecture room to Christian audiences<lb/> That he made application to the <sic>Babtists</sic> or some other Chrisn. denomi<lb/>&#61;nation to take orders for missionary purposes to the south&#44; there are<lb/> other rumors of minor importance which I will not trouble you with but<lb/> request you to give such information as you possess of <persName>Mr. Hs</persName> standing<lb/> and character and of his qualifications for such appointment.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your attention and early reply will be highly appreciated<lb/> by our congregation as well as by</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours very respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Joshua Lazarus</persName> Chairman</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Conc. of investigation</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In replying to your esteemed favor&#44; which came to hand yesterday&#44;<lb/> I beg to state that my knowledge of <persName>Mr Harris</persName> is comparatively of a<lb/> recent date&#44; but during my short acquaintance with him&#44; I never discovered<lb/> aught prejudicial to his moral character.  He visited me repeatedly<lb/> and from the tenor of his conversation&#44; I inferred that he has studied well<lb/> both Hebrew &#38; English.  Regarding his capacity to fill the situation<lb/> for which he has applied&#44; I am utterly unable to pronounce an<lb/> opinion&#44; for I neither heard him recite the prayers&#44; nor deliver a<lb/> sermon.  The two charges brought against <persName>Mr H</persName> would&#44; if<lb/> true&#44; not alone militate against his election&#44; but lower him also in<lb/> the estimation of <hi rend="underline">all</hi> his coreligionists&#59; I trust therefore that they<lb/> may be proved false.  As to myself&#44; I was ignorant of them&#44;<lb/> had I <sic>deem</sic> it my duty on the contrary to state&#44; that a person&#44; who<lb/> had spoken disparagingly of his character in my presence&#44; has&#44; in a<lb/> letter&#44; which I received last week&#44; retracted his accusation</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Believe me etc.</p>
		</body>
